#Text=The Boston Celtics ( 40 - 30 ) defeated the Philadelphia 76ers ( 9 - 61 ) 120 - 105 on Sunday .
#Text=The Sixers are likely one of the best elixirs for a losing streak , and the Celtics were certainly in need of a victory coming into Sunday .
#Text=They 'd lost four consecutive contests , and had seen their playoff seeding slip from third to sixth during that stretch .
#Text=Ultimately , Boston was able to assert its superiority over their hapless hosts , but as has often been the case lately , it did n't happen without a fight from a feisty Sixers squad .
#Text=Even after the Celtics jumped out to a 28 - 16 lead after one period , Philadelphia kept coming , and prevailed over the second and third quarters by a combined margin of 63 - 60 .
#Text=Boston was able to pull away in the final 12 minutes however , and earned the rather hard - fought victory on the strength of solid shooting from all areas of the court .
#Text=The Celtics managed a 49 percent success rate from the field , and 42 percent from three - point range.They were also strong down low , outrebounding the Sixers by a margin of 53 - 40 .
#Text=Boston was unsurprisingly led by Isaiah Thomas , who compiled 26 points , eight assists , six rebounds and a steal .
#Text=Avery Bradley was strong in support , tallying 20 points , four assists , three rebounds , four steals and a block .
#Text=Amir Johnson was a pleasant surprise on offense , registering 18 points , eight rebounds and two blocks .
#Text=Jared Sullinger and Evan Turner rounded out a successful night for the starting five with a pair of 17 - point efforts .
#Text=The former also contributed 13 rebounds , an assist and a steal , while the latter registered nine rebounds and six assists .
#Text=Marcus Smart paced the bench with 15 points , five rebounds , five assists and a pair of steals .
#Text=The Celtics remain in second place in the Eastern Conference 's Atlantic Division , and have moved up to the fifth seed in the conference as well .
#Text=They head back home to face the Orlando Magic on Monday night .
#Text=The Sixers were spearheaded by an outstanding effort off the bench by Carl Landry , who amassed 26 points and eight rebounds over 25 highly efficient minutes .
#Text=Hollis Thompson was next , checking in with 18 points , two assists , a rebound and a block .
#Text=Ish Smith followed with 14 points , eight assists and three rebounds .
#Text=Jerami Grant scored 11 points , and also hauled in eight rebounds , dished out two assists and recorded a pair of blocks .
#Text=Nik Stauskas was the second Sixer to tally double - digit scoring off the bench , totaling 12 points , six rebounds and three assists .
#Text=Philadelphia remains in last place in the Eastern Conference 's Atlantic Division .
#Text=They head to Indiana to take on the Pacers on Monday night .
